  <summary>3/24/1999--Introduced.
Communications Personnel Paperwork Reduction Act of 1999 - Amends the Communications Act of 1934 to direct the Federal Communications Commission (FCC), within 30 days after enactment of this Act, to: (1) repeal specified reporting and recordkeeping requirements; and (2) eliminate any requirement for the disclosure of race, ethnicity, or gender in ownership reporting requirements. Prohibits the FCC from discriminating in employment, or granting any preference in employment, on the basis of race, color, religion, national origin, age, or sex.</summary>
